<p>Update (3/3/2023): Published a <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2076-0760/12/3/148" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">paper</a> based on this work </p><p>Follow-up analysis update (4/2/2023): <a href="https://davidrozado.substack.com/p/openaicms" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">The unequal treatment of demographic groups by ChatGPT/OpenAI content moderation system</a></p><p>On December 6th I <a href="https://davidrozado.substack.com/p/the-political-orientation-of-the" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">published</a> a preliminary analysis showing a left-leaning political bias embedded in the first release of ChatGPT from November 30.</p><p>After the December 15th update of ChatGPT, I <a href="https://davidrozado.substack.com/p/chatgpt" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">replicated my analysis</a> and it appeared as if the political bias had been partially mitigated and the system often strived to provide a multitude of viewpoints for questions with political connotations.</p><p>Thanks for reading Rozado’s Visual Analytics ! Subscribe for free to receive new posts and support my work.</p><p>After the January 9th update of ChatGPT,  I replicated and extended my original analysis by administering 15 political orientation tests to ChatGPT. The moderation of political bias is no longer apparent. 14 out of 15 different political orientation tests diagnose ChatGPT answers to their questions as exhibiting a clear preference to provide left-leaning viewpoints. </p><p>I list next the results of the 15 tests. Each test’s questions and ChatGPT’s answers are provided in the appendix at the end of the article.</p><p><a href="https://www.gotoquiz.com/politics/political-spectrum-quiz.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Political Spectrum Quiz</a> Results</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.co